    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    App
    The main entry point of the Goblin's Keep game.
    Bonus
    Represents a Bonus item that appears temporarily in the game.
    CollisionChecker
    Handles collision detection for entities, including players, enemies, and objects.
    DefaultUI
    Abstract class representing the default UI component in the game.
    Direction
    Represents the four possible movement directions in a 2D space.
    EndUI
    Represents the Game ENDED UI component, displaying the win or lose screen.
    Entity
    Represents a general game entity, serving as the base class for player and enemy characters.
    Exit
    Represents an exit door in the game.
    GamePanel
    The core game panel that manages rendering, game logic, and the game loop.
    GameStatus
    Represents the different states of the game.
    Goblin
    Represents a goblin enemy in the game.
    InstructionsUI
    Represents the instructions UI component, displaying game instructions.
    InvisibleBarrier
    Represents an invisible barrier that the player can touch to trigger the win screen.
    Key
    Represents a key object in the game.
    Lever
    Represents a lever that controls the game's exit gate.
    MainObject
    Represents the base class for all interactive objects in the game.
    MapGenerator
    Generates and loads the game map based on a text file.
    MapHandler
    Controls the game map and tracks game progression.
    MenuInputHandler
    Handles keyboard input for all UI menu systems in the game.
    MenuUI
    Represents the main menu UI component.
    Node
    Represents a node in the pathfinding grid.
    ObjectManager
    Manages all interactive objects in the game.
    Options
    Enum representing the different options available in the game menu.
    pathFinder
    Handles the pathfinding logic for entities in the game.
    PauseUI
    Represents the pause menu UI component.
    Player
    Represents the player character in the game.
    PlayerInputHandler
    Handles keyboard input for player movement.
    RegularGoblin
    Represents a regular goblin entity that can move randomly or follow a path.
    Tile
    Represents a single tile in the game, used by TileManager for rendering the map.
    TileManager
    Handles all types of tiles and maps the image to an array called tile[] and has the draw method for tiles
    Trap
    Represents a trap that deducts points when a player steps on it.
    Tree
    Represents a decorative tree in the game.
    UI
    Represents the main in game UI component for the game, handling both playing and paused states.
